1150  //============================================================================
1151  // Method Description:
1164  template<typename dtype>
1165  NdArray<dtype> append(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<dtype>& inAppendValues, Axis inAxis)
1166  {
1167  switch (inAxis)
1168  {
1169  case Axis::NONE:
1170  {
1171  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inArray.size() + inAppendValues.size());
1172  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
1173  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(), inAppendValues.cend(), returnArray.begin() + inArray.size());
1174 
1175  return returnArray;
1176  }
1177  case Axis::ROW:
1178  {
1179  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
1180  const Shape appendShape = inAppendValues.shape();
1181  if (inShape.cols != appendShape.cols)
1182  {
1183  std::string errStr = "ERROR: append: all the input array dimensions except for the concatenation axis must match exactly";
1184  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1185  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1186  }
1187 
1188  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows + appendShape.rows, inShape.cols);
1189  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
1190  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(), inAppendValues.cend(), returnArray.begin() + inArray.size());
1191 
1192  return returnArray;
1193  }
1194  case Axis::COL:
1195  {
1196  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
1197  const Shape appendShape = inAppendValues.shape();
1198  if (inShape.rows != appendShape.rows)
1199  {
1200  std::string errStr = "ERROR: append: all the input array dimensions except for the concatenation axis must match exactly";
1201  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1202  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1203  }
1204 
1205  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows, inShape.cols + appendShape.cols);
1206  for (uint32 row = 0; row < returnArray.shape().rows; ++row)
1207  {
1208  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), returnArray.begin(row));
1209  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(row), inAppendValues.cend(row), returnArray.begin(row) + inShape.cols);
1210  }
1211 
1212  return returnArray;
1213  }
1214  default:
1215  {
1216  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
1217  // of the compiler warning.
1218  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
1219  }
1220  }
1221  }

1223  //============================================================================
1224  // Method Description:
1243  template<typename dtype>
1244  NdArray<dtype> arange(dtype inStart, dtype inStop, dtype inStep)
1245  {
1246  if (inStep > 0 && inStop < inStart)
1247  {
1248  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: stop value must be larger than the start value for positive step.";
1249  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1250  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1251  }
1252 
1253  if (inStep < 0 && inStop > inStart)
1254  {
1255  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: start value must be larger than the stop value for negative step.";
1256  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1257  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1258  }
1259 
1260  std::vector<dtype> values;
1261 
1262  dtype theValue = inStart;
1263 
1264  if (inStep > 0)
1265  {
1266  while (theValue < inStop)
1267  {
1268  values.push_back(theValue);
1269  theValue += inStep;
1270  }
1271  }
1272  else
1273  {
1274  while (theValue > inStop)
1275  {
1276  values.push_back(theValue);
1277  theValue += inStep;
1278  }
1279  }
1280 
1281  return NdArray<dtype>(values);
1282  }

1307  {
1308  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: stop value must ge greater than 0.";
1309  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1310  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1311  }
1312 
1313  return arange<dtype>(0, inStop, 1);
1314  }

1839  //============================================================================
1840  // Method Description:
1851  template<typename dtype>
1852  NdArray<double> average(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<dtype>& inWeights, Axis inAxis)
1853  {
1854  switch (inAxis)
1855  {
1856  case Axis::NONE:
1857  {
1858  if (inWeights.shape() != inArray.shape())
1859  {
1860  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weight values are not consistant.";
1861  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1862  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1863  }
1864 
1865  NdArray<double> weightedArray(inArray.shape());
1866  std::transform(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), inWeights.cbegin(),
1867  weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1868 
1869  double sum = std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0);
1870  NdArray<double> returnArray = { sum /= inWeights.template astype<double>().sum().item() };
1871 
1872  return returnArray;
1873  }
1874  case Axis::COL:
1875  {
1876  const Shape arrayShape = inArray.shape();
1877  if (inWeights.size() != arrayShape.cols)
1878  {
1879  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weights value are not consistant.";
1880  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1881  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1882  }
1883 
1884  double weightSum = inWeights.template astype<double>().sum().item();
1885  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, arrayShape.rows);
1886  for (uint32 row = 0; row < arrayShape.rows; ++row)
1887  {
1888  NdArray<double> weightedArray(1, arrayShape.cols);
1889  std::transform(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), inWeights.cbegin(),
1890  weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1891 
1892  double sum = std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0);
1893  returnArray(0, row) = sum / weightSum;
1894  }
1895 
1896  return returnArray;
1897  }
1898  case Axis::ROW:
1899  {
1900  if (inWeights.size() != inArray.shape().rows)
1901  {
1902  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weight values are not consistant.";
1903  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1904  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1905  }
1906 
1907  NdArray<dtype> transposedArray = inArray.transpose();
1908 
1909  const Shape transShape = transposedArray.shape();
1910  double weightSum = inWeights.template astype<double>().sum().item();
1911  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, transShape.rows);
1912  for (uint32 row = 0; row < transShape.rows; ++row)
1913  {
1914  NdArray<double> weightedArray(1, transShape.cols);
1915  std::transform(transposedArray.cbegin(row), transposedArray.cend(row), inWeights.cbegin(),
1916  weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1917 
1918  double sum = std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0);
1919  returnArray(0, row) = sum / weightSum;
1920  }
1921 
1922  return returnArray;
1923  }
1924  default:
1925  {
1926  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
1927  // of the compiler warning.
1928  return NdArray<double>(0);
1929  }
1930  }
1931  }

1950  // Method Description:
1967  template<typename dtype>
1968  NdArray<dtype> bincount(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, uint16 inMinLength)
1969  {
1970  // only works with integer input types
1971  static_assert(DtypeInfo<dtype>::isInteger(), "ERROR: bincount: can only use with integer types.");
1972 
1973  dtype maxValue = inArray.max().item();
1974  if (maxValue < 0)
1975  {
1976  // no positive values so just return an empty array
1977  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
1978  }
1979 
1980  if (maxValue + 1 > DtypeInfo<dtype>::max())
1981  {
1982  std::string errStr = "Error: bincount: array values too large, will result in gigantic array that will take up alot of memory...";
1983  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1984  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1985  }
1986 
1987  const uint16 outArraySize = std::max(static_cast<uint16>(maxValue + 1), inMinLength);
1988  NdArray<dtype> clippedArray = inArray.clip(0, maxValue);
1989 
1990  NdArray<dtype> outArray(1, outArraySize);
1991  outArray.zeros();
1992  std::for_each(clippedArray.cbegin(), clippedArray.cend(),
1993  [&outArray](dtype value) noexcept -> void
1994  { ++outArray[value]; });
1995 
1996  return outArray;
1997  }

2255  // Method Description:
2265  template<typename dtype>
2266  NdArray<dtype> column_stack(const std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >& inArrayList)
2267  {
2268  // first loop through to calculate the final size of the array
2269  Shape finalShape;
2270  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
2271  {
2272  if (finalShape.isnull())
2273  {
2274  finalShape = ndarray.shape();
2275  }
2276  else if (ndarray.shape().rows != finalShape.rows)
2277  {
2278  std::string errStr = "ERROR: column_stack: input arrays must have the same number of rows.";
2279  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2280  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2281  }
2282  else
2283  {
2284  finalShape.cols += ndarray.shape().cols;
2285  }
2286  }
2287 
2288  // now that we know the final size, contruct the output array
2289  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(finalShape);
2290  uint32 colStart = 0;
2291  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
2292  {
2293  const Shape theShape = ndarray.shape();
2294  for (uint32 row = 0; row < theShape.rows; ++row)
2295  {
2296  for (uint32 col = 0; col < theShape.cols; ++col)
2297  {
2298  returnArray(row, colStart + col) = ndarray(row, col);
2299  }
2300  }
2301  colStart += theShape.cols;
2302  }
2303 
2304  return returnArray;
2305  }

4025 
4026  if (inSep.compare("") == 0)

4038  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);

4043  fclose(filePtr);

4057  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4058  }

4061 
4062  std::ifstream file(inFilename.c_str());
4063  if (file.is_open())
4064  {

4067  std::string line;
4068  std::getline(file, line);
4069 
4070  std::istringstream iss(line);

4072  {
4073  values.push_back(static_cast<dtype>(std::stod(iss.str())));
4074  }
4075  catch (const std::invalid_argument& ia)
4076  {
4077  std::cout << "Warning: fromfile: " << ia.what() << std::endl;
4079  }
4080  }
4081  file.close();
4082  }
4083  else
4084  {
4085  std::string errStr = "ERROR: fromfile: unable to open file.";

4225  //============================================================================
4226  // Method Description:
4237  template<typename dtype>
4238  NdArray<double> gradient(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, Axis inAxis)
4239  {
4240  switch (inAxis)
4241  {
4242  case Axis::ROW:
4243  {
4244  const auto inShape = inArray.shape();
4245  if (inShape.rows < 2)
4246  {
4247  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 row.";
4248  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4249  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4250  }
4251 
4252  // first do the first and last rows
4253  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(inShape);
4254  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
4255  {
4256  returnArray(0, col) = static_cast<double>(inArray(1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(0, col));
4257  returnArray(-1, col) = static_cast<double>(inArray(-1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(-2, col));
4258  }
4259 
4260  // then rip through the rest of the array
4261  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
4262  {
4263  for (uint32 row = 1; row < inShape.rows - 1; ++row)
4264  {
4265  returnArray(row, col) = (static_cast<double>(inArray(row + 1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row - 1, col))) / 2.0;
4266  }
4267  }
4268 
4269  return returnArray;
4270  }
4271  case Axis::COL:
4272  {
4273  const auto inShape = inArray.shape();
4274  if (inShape.cols < 2)
4275  {
4276  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 columns.";
4277  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4278  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4279  }
4280 
4281  // first do the first and last columns
4282  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(inShape);
4283  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
4284  {
4285  returnArray(row, 0) = static_cast<double>(inArray(row, 1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, 0));
4286  returnArray(row, -1) = static_cast<double>(inArray(row, -1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, -2));
4287  }
4288 
4289  // then rip through the rest of the array
4290  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
4291  {
4292  for (uint32 col = 1; col < inShape.cols - 1; ++col)
4293  {
4294  returnArray(row, col) = (static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col + 1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col - 1))) / 2.0;
4295  }
4296  }
4297 
4298  return returnArray;
4299  }
4300  default:
4301  {
4302  // will return the gradient of the flattened array
4303  if (inArray.size() < 2)
4304  {
4305  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 element.";
4306  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4307  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4308  }
4309 
4310  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(1, inArray.size());
4311  returnArray[0] = static_cast<double>(inArray[1]) - static_cast<double>(inArray[0]);
4312  returnArray[-1] = static_cast<double>(inArray[-1]) - static_cast<double>(inArray[-2]);
4313 
4314  std::transform(inArray.cbegin() + 2, inArray.cend(), inArray.cbegin(), returnArray.begin() + 1,
4315  [](dtype value1, dtype value2) noexcept -> double
4316  { return (static_cast<double>(value1) - static_cast<double>(value2)) / 2.0; });
4317 
4318  return returnArray;
4319  }
4320  }
4321  }

4359  //============================================================================
4360  // Method Description:
4372  template<typename dtype>
4373  std::pair<NdArray<uint32>, NdArray<double> > histogram(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, uint32 inNumBins)
4374  {
4375  if (inNumBins == 0)
4376  {
4377  std::string errStr = "ERROR: histogram: number of bins must be positive.";
4378  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4379  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4380  }
4381 
4382  NdArray<uint32> histo = zeros<uint32>(1, inNumBins);
4383 
4384  const bool useEndPoint = true;
4385  NdArray<double> binEdges = linspace(static_cast<double>(inArray.min().item()),
4386  static_cast<double>(inArray.max().item()), inNumBins + 1, useEndPoint);
4387 
4388  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
4389  {
4390  // binary search to find the bin idx
4391  const bool keepSearching = true;
4392  uint32 lowIdx = 0;
4393  uint32 highIdx = binEdges.size() - 1;
4394  while (keepSearching)
4395  {
4396  const uint32 idx = (lowIdx + highIdx) / 2; // integer division
4397  if (lowIdx == highIdx || lowIdx == highIdx - 1)
4398  {
4399  // we found the bin
4400  ++histo[lowIdx];
4401  break;
4402  }
4403 
4404  if (inArray[i] > binEdges[idx])
4405  {
4406  lowIdx = idx;
4407  }
4408  else if (inArray[i] < binEdges[idx])
4409  {
4410  highIdx = idx;
4411  }
4412  else
4413  {
4414  // we found the bin
4415  ++histo[idx];
4416  break;
4417  }
4418  }
4419  }
4420 
4421  return std::make_pair(histo, binEdges);
4422  }

4540  //============================================================================
4541  // Method Description:
4558  template<typename dtype>
4559  NdArray<dtype> interp(const NdArray<dtype>& inX, const NdArray<dtype>& inXp, const NdArray<dtype>& inFp)
4560  {

4562  if (inXp.size() != inFp.size())
4563  {
4564  std::string errStr = "ERROR: interp: inXp and inFp need to be the same size().";
4565  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4566  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);

4568 
4569  if (inX.min().item() < inXp.min().item() || inX.max().item() > inXp.max().item())
4570  {
4571  std::string errStr = "ERROR: interp: endpoints of inX should be contained within inXp.";
4572  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4573  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4574  }
4575 
4576  // sort the input inXp and inFp data
4577  NdArray<uint32> sortedXpIdxs = argsort(inXp);
4578  NdArray<dtype> sortedXp(1, inFp.size());
4579  NdArray<dtype> sortedFp(1, inFp.size());
4580  uint32 counter = 0;
4581  for (auto sortedXpIdx : sortedXpIdxs)
4582  {
4583  sortedXp[counter] = inXp[sortedXpIdx];
4584  sortedFp[counter++] = inFp[sortedXpIdx];
4585  }
4586 
4587  // sort the input inX array
4588  NdArray<dtype> sortedX = sort(inX);
4589 
4590  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inX.size());
4591 
4592  uint32 currXpIdx = 0;
4593  uint32 currXidx = 0;
4594  while (currXidx < sortedX.size())
4595  {
4596  if (sortedXp[currXpIdx] <= sortedX[currXidx] && sortedX[currXidx] <= sortedXp[currXpIdx + 1])
4597  {
4598  const double percent = static_cast<double>(sortedX[currXidx] - sortedXp[currXpIdx]) /
4599  static_cast<double>(sortedXp[currXpIdx + 1] - sortedXp[currXpIdx]);
4600  returnArray[currXidx++] = utils::interp(sortedFp[currXpIdx], sortedFp[currXpIdx + 1], percent);
4601  }
4602  else
4603  {
4604  ++currXpIdx;
4605  }
4606  }
4607 
4608  return returnArray;
4609  }

4938  {

4940  {
4941  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
4942  }
4943  else if (inNum == 1)
4944  {
4945  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart };
4946  return returnArray;
4947  }
4948 
4949  if (inStop <= inStart)
4950  {
4951  std::string errStr = "ERROR: linspace: stop value must be greater than the start value.";
4952  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4953  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4954  }
4955 
4956  if (endPoint)
4957  {
4958  if (inNum == 2)
4959  {
4960  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart, inStop };
4961  return returnArray;
4962  }
4963  else
4964  {
4965  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inNum);
4966  returnArray[0] = inStart;
4967  returnArray[inNum - 1] = inStop;
4968 
4969  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / (inNum - 1);
4970  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inNum - 1; ++i)
4971  {
4972  returnArray[i] = returnArray[i - 1] + step;
4973  }
4974 
4975  return returnArray;
4976  }
4977  }
4978  else
4979  {
4980  if (inNum == 2)
4981  {
4982  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / (inNum);
4983  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart, inStart + step };
4984  return returnArray;
4985  }
4986  else
4987  {
4988  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inNum);
4989  returnArray[0] = inStart;
4990 
4991  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / inNum;
4992  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inNum; ++i)

5850  // Method Description:

5863  NdArray<dtype> nanpercentile(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, double inPercentile,
5864  Axis inAxis, const std::string& inInterpMethod)
5865  {
5866  if (inPercentile < 0.0 || inPercentile > 100.0)
5867  {
5868  std::string errStr = "ERROR: percentile: input percentile value must be of the range [0, 100].";
5869  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
5870  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
5871  }
5872 
5873  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") != 0 &&
5874  inInterpMethod.compare("lower") != 0 &&
5875  inInterpMethod.compare("higher") != 0 &&
5876  inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") != 0 &&
5877  inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") != 0)
5878  {
5879  std::string errStr = "ERROR: percentile: input interpolation method is not a vaid option.\n";
5880  errStr += "\tValid options are 'linear', 'lower', 'higher', 'nearest', 'midpoint'.";
5881  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
5882  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
5883  }
5884 
5885  switch (inAxis)
5886  {
5887  case Axis::NONE:
5888  {
5889  if (utils::essentiallyEqual(inPercentile, 0.0))
5890  {
5891  for (auto value : inArray)
5892  {
5893  if (!isnan(value))
5894  {
5895  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { value };
5896  return returnArray;
5897  }
5898  }
5899  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
5900  }
5901  else if (utils::essentiallyEqual(inPercentile, 100.0))
5902  {
5903  for (int32 i = static_cast<int32>(inArray.size()) - 1; i > -1; --i)
5904  {
5905  if (!isnan(inArray[i]))
5906  {
5907  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inArray[i] };
5908  return returnArray;
5909  }
5910  }
5911  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
5912  }
5913 
5914  std::vector<double> arrayCopy;
5915  uint32 numNonNan = 0;
5916  for (auto value : inArray)
5917  {
5918  if (!isnan(value))
5919  {
5920  arrayCopy.push_back(value);
5921  ++numNonNan;
5922  }
5923  }
5924 
5925  if (arrayCopy.size() < 2)
5926  {
5927  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
5928  }
5929 
5930  const int32 i = static_cast<int32>(std::floor(static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1) * inPercentile / 100.0));
5931  const uint32 indexLower = static_cast<uint32>(clip<uint32>(i, 0, numNonNan - 2));
5932 
5933  std::sort(arrayCopy.begin(), arrayCopy.end());
5934 
5935  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") == 0)
5936  {
5937  const double percentI = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5938  const double fraction = (inPercentile / 100.0 - percentI) /
5939  (static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1) - percentI);
5940 
5941  const double returnValue = arrayCopy[indexLower] + (arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] - arrayCopy[indexLower]) * fraction;
5942  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { returnValue };
5943  return returnArray;
5944  }
5945  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("lower") == 0)
5946  {
5947  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower] };
5948  return returnArray;
5949  }
5950  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("higher") == 0)
5951  {
5952  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] };
5953  return returnArray;
5954  }
5955  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") == 0)
5956  {
5957  const double percent = inPercentile / 100.0;
5958  const double percent1 = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5959  const double percent2 = static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5960  const double diff1 = percent - percent1;
5961  const double diff2 = percent2 - percent;
5962 
5963  switch (argmin<double>({ diff1, diff2 }).item())
5964  {
5965  case 0:
5966  {
5967  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower] };
5968  return returnArray;
5969  }
5970  case 1:
5971  {
5972  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] };
5973  return returnArray;
5974  }
5975  }
5976  }
5977  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") == 0)
5978  {
5979  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { (arrayCopy[indexLower] + arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) / 2.0 };
5980  return returnArray;
5981  }
5982  }
5983  case Axis::COL:
5984  {
5985  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
5986 
5987  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5988  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5989  {
5990  NdArray<dtype> outValue = nanpercentile(NdArray<dtype>(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row)),
5991  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod);
5992 
5993  if (outValue.size() == 1)
5994  {
5995  returnArray[row] = outValue.item();
5996  }
5997  else
5998  {
5999  returnArray[row] = constants::nan;
6000  }
6001  }
6002 
6003  return returnArray;
6004  }
6005  case Axis::ROW:
6006  {
6007  NdArray<dtype> arrayTrans = inArray.transpose();
6008  const Shape inShape = arrayTrans.shape();
6009 
6010  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6011  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6012  {
6013  NdArray<dtype> outValue = nanpercentile(NdArray<dtype>(arrayTrans.cbegin(row), arrayTrans.cend(row)),
6014  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod);
6015 
6016  if (outValue.size() == 1)
6017  {
6018  returnArray[row] = outValue.item();
6019  }
6020  else
6021  {
6022  returnArray[row] = constants::nan;
6023  }
6024  }
6025

6028  default:

6573 
6574  const double returnValue = arrayCopy[indexLower] + (arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] - arrayCopy[indexLower]) * fraction;
6575  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { returnValue };
6576  return returnArray;
6577  }
6578  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("lower") == 0)
6579  {
6580  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower] };
6581  return returnArray;
6582  }
6583  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("higher") == 0)
6584  {
6585  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] };
6586  return returnArray;
6587  }
6588  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") == 0)
6589  {
6590  const double percent = inPercentile / 100.0;
6591  const double percent1 = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(inArray.size() - 1);
6592  const double percent2 = static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(inArray.size() - 1);
6593  const double diff1 = percent - percent1;
6594  const double diff2 = percent2 - percent;
6595 
6596  switch (argmin<double>({ diff1, diff2 }).item())
6597  {
6598  case 0:
6599  {
6600  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower] };
6601  return returnArray;
6602  }
6603  case 1:
6604  {
6605  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] };
6606  return returnArray;
6607  }
6608  }
6609  }
6610  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") == 0)
6611  {
6612  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { static_cast<dtype>((arrayCopy[indexLower] + arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) / 2.0) };
6613  return returnArray;
6614  }
6615  }
6616  case Axis::COL:
6617  {
6618  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
6619 
6620  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6621  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6622  {
6623  returnArray[row] = percentile(NdArray<dtype>(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row)),
6624  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod).item();
6625  }
6626 
6627  return returnArray;
6628  }
6629  case Axis::ROW:
6630  {
6631  NdArray<dtype> arrayTrans = inArray.transpose();
6632  const Shape inShape = arrayTrans.shape();
6633 
6634  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6635  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6636  {
6637  returnArray[row] = percentile(NdArray<dtype>(arrayTrans.cbegin(row), arrayTrans.cend(row)),
6638  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod).item();
6639  }
6640 
6641  return returnArray;
6642  }
6643  default:
6644  {
6645  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
6646  // of the compiler warning.
6647  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
6648  }
6649  }
6650  }

7303  template<typename dtype>
7304  NdArray<dtype> roll(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, int32 inShift, Axis inAxis) noexcept
7305  {
7306  switch (inAxis)
7307  {
7308  case Axis::NONE:
7309  {
7310  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inArray.size();
7311  if (inShift > 0)
7312  {
7313  shift = inArray.size() - shift;
7314  }
7315 
7316  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inArray);
7317  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(), returnArray.begin() + shift, returnArray.end());
7318 
7319  return returnArray;
7320  }
7321  case Axis::COL:
7322  {
7323  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
7324 
7325  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inShape.cols;
7326  if (inShift > 0)
7327  {
7328  shift = inShape.cols - shift;
7329  }
7330 
7331  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inArray);
7332  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
7333  {
7334  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(row), returnArray.begin(row) + shift, returnArray.end(row));
7335  }
7336 
7337  return returnArray;
7338  }
7339  case Axis::ROW:
7340  {
7341  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
7342 
7343  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inShape.rows;
7344  if (inShift > 0)
7345  {
7346  shift = inShape.rows - shift;
7347  }
7348 
7349  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = inArray.transpose();
7350  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.cols; ++row)
7351  {
7352  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(row), returnArray.begin(row) + shift, returnArray.end(row));
7353  }
7354 
7355  return returnArray.transpose();
7356  }
7357  default:
7358  {

7360  // of the compiler warning.

7438  //============================================================================
7439  // Method Description:
7448  template<typename dtype>
7449  NdArray<dtype> row_stack(const std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >& inArrayList)
7450  {
7451  // first loop through to calculate the final size of the array
7452  Shape finalShape;
7453  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
7454  {
7455  if (finalShape.isnull())
7456  {
7457  finalShape = ndarray.shape();
7458  }
7459  else if (ndarray.shape().cols != finalShape.cols)
7460  {
7461  std::string errStr = "ERROR: row_stack: input arrays must have the same number of columns.";
7462  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
7463  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
7464  }
7465  else
7466  {
7467  finalShape.rows += ndarray.shape().rows;
7468  }
7469  }
7470 
7471  // now that we know the final size, contruct the output array
7472  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(finalShape);
7473  uint32 rowStart = 0;
7474  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
7475  {
7476  const Shape theShape = ndarray.shape();
7477  for (uint32 row = 0; row < theShape.rows; ++row)
7478  {
7479  for (uint32 col = 0; col < theShape.cols; ++col)
7480  {
7481  returnArray(rowStart + row, col) = ndarray(row, col);
7482  }
7483  }
7484  rowStart += theShape.rows;
7485  }
7486 
7487  return returnArray;
7488  }

8139  template<typename dtype>
8140  NdArray<double> trapz(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, double dx, Axis inAxis) noexcept
8141  {
8142  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
8143  switch (inAxis)
8144  {
8145  case Axis::COL:
8146  {
8147  NdArray<double> returnArray(inShape.rows, 1);
8148  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
8149  {
8150  double sum = 0;
8151  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols - 1; ++col)
8152  {
8153  sum += static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col + 1) - inArray(row, col)) / 2.0 +
8154  static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col));
8155  }
8156 
8157  returnArray[row] = sum * dx;
8158  }
8159 
8160  return returnArray;
8161  }
8162  case Axis::ROW:
8163  {
8164  NdArray<dtype> arrayTranspose = inArray.transpose();
8165  const Shape transShape = arrayTranspose.shape();
8166  NdArray<double> returnArray(transShape.rows, 1);
8167  for (uint32 row = 0; row < transShape.rows; ++row)
8168  {
8169  double sum = 0;
8170  for (uint32 col = 0; col < transShape.cols - 1; ++col)
8171  {
8172  sum += static_cast<double>(arrayTranspose(row, col + 1) - arrayTranspose(row, col)) / 2.0 +
8173  static_cast<double>(arrayTranspose(row, col));
8174  }
8175 
8176  returnArray[row] = sum * dx;
8177  }
8178 
8179  return returnArray;
8180  }
8181  case Axis::NONE:
8182  {
8183  double sum = 0.0;
8184  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size() - 1; ++i)
8185  {
8186  sum += static_cast<double>(inArray[i + 1] - inArray[i]) / 2.0 + static_cast<double>(inArray[i]);
8187  }
8188 
8189  NdArray<double> returnArray = { sum * dx };
8190  return returnArray;
8191  }
8192  default:
8193  {
8194  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
8195  // of the compiler warning.
8196  return NdArray<double>(0);
8197  }
8198  }
8199  }

8500  //============================================================================
8501  // Method Description:
8512  template<typename dtype>
8513  NdArray<dtype> trim_zeros(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const std::string inTrim)
8514  {
8515  if (inTrim == "f")
8516  {
8517  uint32 place = 0;
8518  for (auto value : inArray)
8519  {
8520  if (value != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8521  {
8522  break;
8523  }
8524  else
8525  {
8526  ++place;
8527  }
8528  }
8529 
8530  if (place == inArray.size())
8531  {
8532  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8533  }
8534 
8535  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inArray.size() - place);
8536  std::copy(inArray.cbegin() + place, inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
8537 
8538  return returnArray;
8539  }
8540  else if (inTrim == "b")
8541  {
8542  uint32 place = inArray.size();
8543  for (uint32 i = inArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i)
8544  {
8545  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8546  {
8547  break;
8548  }
8549  else
8550  {
8551  --place;
8552  }
8553  }
8554 
8555  if (place == 0 || (place == 1 && inArray[0] == 0))
8556  {
8557  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8558  }
8559 
8560  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, place);
8561  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cbegin() + place, returnArray.begin());
8562 
8563  return returnArray;
8564  }
8565  else if (inTrim == "fb")
8566  {
8567  uint32 placeBegin = 0;
8568  for (auto value : inArray)
8569  {
8570  if (value != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8571  {
8572  break;
8573  }
8574  else
8575  {
8576  ++placeBegin;
8577  }
8578  }
8579 
8580  if (placeBegin == inArray.size())
8581  {
8582  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8583  }
8584 
8585  uint32 placeEnd = inArray.size();
8586  for (uint32 i = inArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i)
8587  {
8588  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8589  {
8590  break;
8591  }
8592  else
8593  {
8594  --placeEnd;
8595  }
8596  }
8597 
8598  if (placeEnd == 0 || (placeEnd == 1 && inArray[0] == 0))
8599  {
8600  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8601  }
8602 
8603  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, placeEnd - placeBegin);
8604  std::copy(inArray.cbegin() + placeBegin, inArray.cbegin() + placeEnd, returnArray.begin());
8605 
8606  return returnArray;
8607  }
8608  else
8609  {
8610  std::string errStr = "ERROR: trim_zeros: trim options are 'f' = front, 'b' = back, 'fb' = front and back.";
8611  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
8612  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
8613  }
8614  }

8788  // Method Description:
8800  template<typename dtype>
8801  NdArray<dtype> where(const NdArray<bool>& inMask, const NdArray<dtype>& inA, const NdArray<dtype>& inB)
8802  {
8803  const auto shapeMask = inMask.shape();
8804  const auto shapeA = inA.shape();
8805  if (shapeA != inB.shape())
8806  {
8807  std::string errStr = "ERROR: where: input inA and inB must be the same shapes.";
8808  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
8809  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
8810  }
8811 
8812  if (shapeMask != shapeA)
8813  {
8814  std::string errStr = "ERROR: where: input inMask must be the same shape as the input arrays.";
8815  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
8816  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
8817  }
8818 
8819  auto outArray = NdArray<dtype>(shapeMask);
8820 
8821  uint32 idx = 0;
8822  for (auto maskValue : inMask)
8823  {
8824  if (maskValue)
8825  {
8826  outArray[idx] = inA[idx];
8827  }
8828  else
8829  {
8830  outArray[idx] = inB[idx];
8831  }
8832  ++idx;
8833  }
8834 
8835  return outArray;
8836  }
